Sentencas: The composite cathode system is examined for suitability on a Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-delta electrolyte based solid oxide fuel cell at intermediate temperatures (500-700 degrees C).
Titulo: Characterization of the 75% Gd0.8Sr0.2CoO3-δ/25% Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ composite cathode system for use in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cathode is characterized for electronic conductivity and area specific charge transfer resistance.
Titulo: Characterization of the 75% Gd0.8Sr0.2CoO3-δ/25% Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ composite cathode system for use in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This cathode system is chosen for its excellent thermal expansion match to the electrolyte, its relatively high conductivity (115 S cm(-1) at 700 degrees C), and its low activation energy for oxygen reduction (99 kJ mol(-1)).
Titulo: Characterization of the 75% Gd0.8Sr0.2CoO3-δ/25% Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ composite cathode system for use in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is found that the decrease of sintering temperature of the composite cathode system produces a significant decrease in charge transfer resistances to as low as 0.25 Omega cm(2).
Titulo: Characterization of the 75% Gd0.8Sr0.2CoO3-δ/25% Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ composite cathode system for use in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The conductivity of the cathode systems is between 40 and 88 S cm(-1) for open porosities of 30-40%.
Titulo: Characterization of the 75% Gd0.8Sr0.2CoO3-δ/25% Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ composite cathode system for use in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
